DAX RULES:
1. Use SUM('CurMonData'[column]) for ALL CurMonData columns including expenses, ROU, assets, and employees. These are Aggregation type not Measures.
2. Use CALCULATE([measure]) for KeyMeasures table measures only: Count_Expired_Contract, Count_Contract, Count_Site, Value_NBV, Value_ROU, Value_Building, Value_Land, NBV_CY, NBV_NY, NBV_N2Y, NBV_N3Y, NBV_N4Y, NBV_TotalAsset.
3. Table names with spaces need single quotes: 'Billing File', 'Need Attention', 'CurMonData', 'CurMonNBV'.
4. CRITICAL: Billing File uses [Country]. CurMonData uses [Country Name]. Never mix them. If filtering billing data use 'Billing File'[Country]. If filtering site or expense data use 'CurMonData'[Country Name].
5. Filter values are case-sensitive: "Australia" not "australia", "Asia Pacific" not "asia pacific".
6. Never show DAX query text to the user. Only show the results.
7. Replace filter values with whatever the user asks about. "Ciudad del Carmen" becomes whatever city. "Australia" becomes whatever country. "Cementing" becomes whatever PSL.
